{"id_resto": "g186338-d1386832", "id_comment": "g186338-d1386832-r347557109", "resto": "Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d1386832-Reviews-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "rating": "2", "title": "Ok to eat if you are staying at Hilton, but not worth coming here if you aren't staying at the Hilton ", "diner_date": " February 2016", "rating_date": "14 February 2016", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "mcsc-squared", "reviewer_origin": ["New York City, New York"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "918"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "226"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d1386832-r347557109-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "content": ["Ok to eat if you are staying at Hilton, but not worth coming here if you aren't staying at the Hilton. Average food. Average service. First question they ask - are you staying with us ... Is that supposed to make a difference?? Why not just seat people and give them a menu? They got the appetizer and main course together - huh?? Not worth the trouble"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d1386832", "id_comment": "g186338-d1386832-r347824497", "resto": "Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d1386832-Reviews-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Glad I didn't listen to the bad reviews", "diner_date": " February 2016", "rating_date": "15 February 2016", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Hannah O", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "19"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "7"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Service"], "other_ratings_value": ["40"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d1386832-r347824497-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "content": ["My boyfriend booked here for a pre-valentines meal and I took it upon myself to check it out before (OCD behaviour). Anyway after reading the reviews I was adamant I did not want to go here. My boyfriend being him said nope we are going - end of. ", "I am beyond glad we went! The service, the food, the company, the ambience, everything was just fabulous. Only one thing though, I hate sitting on the front line (by the windows) where people can see you. However it was like 8pm so foot traffic was practically non-existent. ", "The waiter assisted me in choosing a red wine and was ever so helpful in suggestions and explaining the background of each label followed by a sample. When chosen they ensured that our glasses were topped up.", "In between courses they kept the table topped up with bread. The starters; I had the salmon which was absolutely lush (and I am not a great fan of cold fish) and he had the ham hock (didn't look appealing to me but tried it minus the eggs and it actually was quite nice.", "The mains I had the halloumi cheese with salsa and onion rings- nice big chunks of halloumi. Slightly overdone but I didn't mind as the saltiness of halloumi can be a bit overwhelming. The onions rings were perfect and nicely sized. Very filling overall. He had the surf and turf. Nicely sized prawns although they were not entirely fresh but you can only tell if you are a prawn fan like me. He had chips on the side. This definitely was not your typical type of chips. You could tell they were hand cut as they resembled wedges more than chips. ", "The overall ambience was nice. It was soooo toasty. Normally being sat by the window always brings a draught. But it was very cosy. As it was an evening the restaurant was full but not packed at all. You still had the traffic of the hotel in the bar area which is just before the restaurant part. It was quiet enough to have a conversation and loud enough to mask your conversation also. ", "Didn't have dessert as I was very full on the 2 courses. But the options weren't nothing enticing anyway. ", "Least dislike was the lady once forget something we asked for and my fella had to go over to reception to get her attention. Liked our waiter the most..he made the whole experience pleasurable. Can't remember his name but he was a French, tall black man."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d1386832", "id_comment": "g186338-d1386832-r349260234", "resto": "Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d1386832-Reviews-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "rating": "2", "title": "High tea experience. Just ok.", "diner_date": null, "rating_date": "19 February 2016", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "alexandroslondon", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "28"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "15"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Service"], "other_ratings_value": ["40"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d1386832-r349260234-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "content": ["I had an high tea for two.", "It was said we should have a champagne but we had just a strawberry prosecco.", "The savouries were just ok the sweets were all good but maybe not enough. Portions were really small compared to other locations. Coffee wasn't really good.", "Staff just asked once if we wanted a refill. Btw really friendly and kind."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d1386832", "id_comment": "g186338-d1386832-r349354175", "resto": "Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d1386832-Reviews-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "rating": "1", "title": "Afternoon tea in January", "diner_date": null, "rating_date": "20 February 2016", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Lynn G", "reviewer_origin": ["Sutton Coldfield, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "1"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service"], "other_ratings_value": ["20", "20"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d1386832-r349354175-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "content": ["This is a subsequent review. We gave constructive feedback to Armand at the hotel and received a response offering a complimentary tea due to our initial less than praiseworthy experience. We declined this kind offer due to logistics but thanked him anyway. To our surprise we receive a further email from a lady called Jan from Hilton worldwide in response to our constructive feedback. She was to send a fifty dollar credit card for our use. We were not looking for financial gain but we responded thanking. Her for her gesture of goodwill.Two to three weeks later we still had not received any card so we emailed just to say that we had not received anything from the Hilton. There may have been a problem but we were not expecting the next Hilton email from a guy called Tony at HIlton worldwide. He emailed to say that he had no proof of any experience that ww had engaged in previously and had declined the credit card which was to be forwarded to our personal address. His assessment was that it was a misunderstanding. It is embarrassing to receive such reply and to put into question out credibility and honesty even though the paper trail of all the encounters was also forwarded to this gentlemen on the same occasion. ", "Our afternoon tea experience was bought as ta Christmas present from our son in law who is a Hilton diamond member.", "We have replied to Tony requesting that he now let's us have details of the Chief executive officer of the Hilton worldwide in order that we may vindicate ourselves from the extraordinary predicament and embarrassment we find ourselves.", "The whole matter is like having a sledgehammer to crack a walnut and none of this is our own making.", "As far as we are concerned this is not to gain financially, rest assured.", "However,we need to make future guests aware of our experience in order that they do not have to deal with the nightmare scenario which has enveloped our life.", "We now fight for the principle of being treated as valuable customers"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d1386832", "id_comment": "g186338-d1386832-r358998232", "resto": "Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d1386832-Reviews-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "rating": "2", "title": "Afternoon tea", "diner_date": " March 2016", "rating_date": "27 March 2016", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "keeley123456789", "reviewer_origin": ["Dagenham, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "32"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "21"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d1386832-r358998232-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "content": ["I went to the afternoon tea today and would not return. There was no atmosphere and terrible service. We got told where to sit, even though there was one other table occupied in the whole restaurant. At the busiest there was 5 tables of 2 people including us but took over 20 minutes for anyone to notice me to get a glass of water. No refill of tea, nor even offered. Food was okay, but just okay.", "Def the worst afternoon tea I have attended."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d1386832", "id_comment": "g186338-d1386832-r362595550", "resto": "Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d1386832-Reviews-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "rating": "2", "title": "Not the best at all", "diner_date": " April 2016", "rating_date": "8 April 2016", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "sabau", "reviewer_origin": ["Brighton, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "53"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "26"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d1386832-r362595550-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "content": ["For being part of the Hilton, is not at all what you expect. Food was tasteless, minute steak for 24.00GBP doesn't worth and do not do the job..", " I was looking for something special and I got the wow effect... but in the wrong way. Staff also not that professional. Expected better from them"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d1386832", "id_comment": "g186338-d1386832-r345507622", "resto": "Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d1386832-Reviews-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "disappointing", "diner_date": " February 2016", "rating_date": "7 February 2016", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "991Marina", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "211"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "88"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d1386832-r345507622-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "content": ["I went with friends for afternoon tea and we were excited as we were going in a restaurant at the Hilton Hotel.But we were a bit disappointed by the end of the afternoon.", "The food was really nice and tasty but the atmosphere was a bit \"flat\",there wasn't a tea menu,as I had in other restaurants, and were only offered English breakfast tea. The waitress only spoke to us at the beginning to show as the table and never come ones to ask how things were. I won't go back there for afternoon tea."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d1386832", "id_comment": "g186338-d1386832-r294185149", "resto": "Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d1386832-Reviews-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "Average", "diner_date": " July 2015", "rating_date": "30 July 2015", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Mohsoldier", "reviewer_origin": ["Kelty, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "152"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "61"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d1386832-r294185149-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "content": ["Convenient if staying at the hotel with an reasonable menu including fish, steaks, burgers etc. Nice atmosphere but never seems to be busy, assume this is down to some very good restaurants around the hotel"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d1386832", "id_comment": "g186338-d1386832-r321009704", "resto": "Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d1386832-Reviews-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "rating": "2", "title": "Overpriced and average food at best", "diner_date": " October 2015", "rating_date": "22 October 2015", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Chad P", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "1"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "2"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d1386832-r321009704-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "content": ["I don't normally feel compelled to write reviews, but did this time after having dinner at Cinnamon. We were the only people in the restaurant at 9:00pm on a Thursday night...maybe that should have told us something. ", "First, I asked the waiter about the Ox Cheek entree, and his response was, \"I would stay away from that\". No problem, I ordered the surf and turf instead...steak and prawns. ", "The steak was ok, not horrible but maybe average. Part of it was very chewy. The prawns were a whole different story. Typically when I think of prawns, I think of something bigger than a shrimp. I know prawns can be small as well, and these definitely were...very small. And they were so over cooked and rock hard that I could barely cut through one of them with a steak knife. ", "The waiter did agree that they looked \"bad\" and asked the chef to make more. More were brought out, again very small, but at least properly cooked this time. Only downfall is that a few of them still had the veins clearly showing. ", "Beyond that my wife's entree was small and her side of mashed potatoes were very bland and lacked any flavor. ", "To top it all off, the price was a little high especially considering the lack of quality of the food. 2 entrees, 2 sides, a glass of wine, and a glass of beer came out to 76 pounds with tip. I have had much better meals elsewhere in London for half of that cost. ", "We are staying at this Hilton for 3 nights, but do not plan on eating here again. "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d1386832", "id_comment": "g186338-d1386832-r345161523", "resto": "Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d1386832-Reviews-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Amazing", "diner_date": " February 2016", "rating_date": "5 February 2016", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "mary s", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "19"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "11"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d1386832-r345161523-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "content": ["A friend and I had surf & turf with cut chips. You hardly had to cut the steak. Wine and bread both really good. The service was very good too."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d1386832", "id_comment": "g186338-d1386832-r305934655", "resto": "Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d1386832-Reviews-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Family birthdays", "diner_date": " February 2015", "rating_date": "1 September 2015", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "KRGA_12", "reviewer_origin": ["Truro, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "31"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "9"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d1386832-r305934655-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "content": ["Good all round food.", "We were celebrating 2 birthdays and we were served perfectly and with great care."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d1386832", "id_comment": "g186338-d1386832-r294796947", "resto": "Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d1386832-Reviews-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "rating": "2", "title": "Tea Bag used", "diner_date": " August 2015", "rating_date": "1 August 2015", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "oldbid48", "reviewer_origin": ["Hadleigh, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "34"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "25"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["20", "20", "20"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d1386832-r294796947-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "content": ["Used a groupon offer today for High Tea. I have had at least one dozen high Teas in London and this rates fairly low down. We wandered around the hotel for some time before anybody acknowledged us. The waitress was polite enough.I requested tea and was offered no choice whatsoever. Usually that is the highlight of High Tea when you are allowed to pick from dozens of different teas. When our tea was brought up she said we could have refills whenever we wanted but we never saw her again,even when we left our table. I could not believe my eyes when I saw the string and tag hanging out of the teapot.!!! This is supposed to be The Hilton Hotel. A top class hotel! and a teabag!!!?? The resulting tea was like dishwater but we could not see the waitress to even complain about it.Some of the sandwiches were stale. the one scone we had each was the size of a 50p piece. We were given enough cream to cover at least half dozen that size. The cakes were ok. So very disappointed as this was a gift to my guest. We finished our meal and got up and left and there wasn't a single member of staff around. Not impressed at all."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d1386832", "id_comment": "g186338-d1386832-r308877815", "resto": "Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d1386832-Reviews-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Good selection", "diner_date": " September 2015", "rating_date": "10 September 2015", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "karthryn D", "reviewer_origin": ["Newbury, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "3"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d1386832-r308877815-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "content": ["Good selection of foods - Standard breakfast fare but very fresh and tasty. Staff were so pleasant too."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d1386832", "id_comment": "g186338-d1386832-r313653025", "resto": "Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d1386832-Reviews-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "rating": "2", "title": "Disappointed ", "diner_date": " September 2015", "rating_date": "25 September 2015", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Moskon", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "174"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "62"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d1386832-r313653025-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "content": ["We bought afternoon tea vouchers off groupon. This was my first time going for an afternoon tea and was so disappointed. The atmosphere was not relaxed/cosy. It was very modern and upright. They first served the tea and after a while the snacks came. The bread if the sandwiches had gone tiny bit stale which means they'd made it from before. I really liked the Victoria sponge cake and this other thing don't know what it's called but had fruits and jelly in a crust. W another negative thing is they only had time slots between 1-3 which is very odd because that's lunchtime! I have tea around 5. So it was very awkward we couldn't decide if we should have an early lunch. But then we would be too full. When we saw the snacks we were thinking we're gonna wipe it clean but in actual fact it was very filling and we couldn't finish it off had so much left over. Overall I think afternoon tea should be cosier more homey and definitely not at 1pm!!after this o went to another afternoon tea in Scunthorpe called giles absolutely loves it it was very vintage deco everything suited. Was such a lovely tea room. "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d1386832", "id_comment": "g186338-d1386832-r332451822", "resto": "Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d1386832-Reviews-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "rating": "1", "title": "Bad service ", "diner_date": " December 2015", "rating_date": "13 December 2015", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "piera26", "reviewer_origin": ["Brighton, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "3"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "2"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d1386832-r332451822-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "content": ["Food took over an hour to come, when it arrived parts of the order was missing, burger ordered with cheese and bacon only come out with bacon. Peppercorn sauce with the steak which the steak went cold before the sauce come out.. Not the correct salad ordered so had to be replaced. Helpful lady when complained and was compensated us but a shame as it was a special birthday for my nan. Very disappointing X "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d1386832", "id_comment": "g186338-d1386832-r334106721", "resto": "Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d1386832-Reviews-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "rating": "1", "title": "90th Birthday Treat For Mum 13th December 2015", "diner_date": " December 2015", "rating_date": "20 December 2015", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "39eileenh48", "reviewer_origin": ["Harlow, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "4"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "1"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Service"], "other_ratings_value": ["10"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d1386832-r334106721-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "content": ["Seven of us came here using Groupon Vouchers and were joined by another three who were going to choose and pay of the menu.This was to be a treat for my mums 90th birthday which l told the receptionist when l booked the table but when we arrived we were shown to a large table that had benches around it, not at all suitable for my old mum and had to get them to remove a bench and replace with a suitable chair. Our order took over an hour to arrive and just came in dribs and drabs with the fries and pepper sauces turning up as people were finishing there small steaks. Mine and mums seabass was very tasty but again my fries and her mash potato turned up as we were nearly finishing our meal.I know restaurants like to cook vegetables al'denta but the portion of vegetables my mum were given were almost raw. l was served the wrong salad and by the time the correct salad arrived l had finished my meal. I was bitterly disappointed as l wanted it to be special for her. I felt that as we were using vouchers the staff were not really interested in us, although very polite they were just not bothered.We were not offered a desert menu or asked if we wanted more drinks .The rest of the family who had ordered off the main menu were equally disappointed and were told that they would not be charged. But as we had paid upfront with Groupon were offered nothing. To make matters worse we were the only ones in the restaurant that day and when it came to us leaving the staff had all disappeared without a word of apology. NEVER AGAIN... ", " A PLACE TO AVOID"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d1386832", "id_comment": "g186338-d1386832-r344027417", "resto": "Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d1386832-Reviews-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Afternoon tea", "diner_date": " January 2016", "rating_date": "31 January 2016", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "izabelllcia", "reviewer_origin": ["Ruislip, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "1"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d1386832-r344027417-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "content": ["My boyfriend and I were bought an afternoon tea experience at the Hilton in Canary Wharf. It was fantastic. The service was flawless, especially Hanimcan. Her and her manager were very attentive and helpful when we an issue with our voucher. "]}
