{"id_resto": "g186338-d1386832", "id_comment": "g186338-d1386832-r145919700", "resto": "Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d1386832-Reviews-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "rating": "2", "title": "Would not recommend it!", "diner_date": " November 2012", "rating_date": "21 November 2012", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "sanbran", "reviewer_origin": ["Bournemouth, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "115"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "68"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Atmosphere", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["10", "20", "40", "20"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d1386832-r145919700-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "content": ["Stayed at the hotel for the week-end of my birthday, had been out all day so decided to stay in and eat downstairs in the restaurant. Our starters lacked any kick, unlike the description given on the menu and my vegetables arrived cold. The chicken was very hot but just gave up and eat it all and told the waitress to inform the kitchen they need to review their handling of sending out items that had been standing around. This idea of serving on slate squares does not help, if the quality of the food is not up to much. We declined free desserts and just opted for a complimentary coffee. They removed the vegetables from the bill but it still came to a hefty sum. Spoilt the end of the day really, but must compliment the waitress on her handling of the whole situation, just the kitchen at fault. Big shame really, as the breakfast there has always been and still is fantastic."]}
