{"id_resto": "g186338-d1386832", "id_comment": "g186338-d1386832-r138564534", "resto": "Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d1386832-Reviews-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Hilton Canary Wharf's in-house restaurant", "diner_date": " April 2012", "rating_date": "27 August 2012", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "gorpalm", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "45"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "94"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d1386832-r138564534-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "content": ["For a hotel restaurant its exemplifies what you want out of your conscious choice in choosing a hotel restaurant outside of breakfast time - Safe, dependable, decent food, decent service. ", "Its breakfast service is still brilliant - Great service, fast refills of coffee, good food quality. Choice has been trimmed a little - No more wheatgrass juice for example, one of the interesting offerings they had the first time I had breakfast there. ", "If you're staying at the hotel and its bad weather outside then its a natural choice; if it isnt then its harder to justify not wandering out to Canary Wharf close-by."]}
