{"id_resto": "g186338-d1386832", "id_comment": "g186338-d1386832-r119000494", "resto": "Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d1386832-Reviews-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Nice place for fusion food - and quite good service", "diner_date": " October 2011", "rating_date": "6 October 2011", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "CarosassoneCH", "reviewer_origin": ["Fribourg, Switzerland"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "74"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "73"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Atmosphere", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "50", "40", "40"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d1386832-r119000494-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "content": ["I had dinner at the Cinnamon with a customer and a colleague, both of Indian descent. The Cinnamon offers fusion food - in our case to a fusion group ;-). It's a nice place and you can host any kind of customer without any problem - even demanding ones...", "The food is nice and you should order a mixed starter platter if you want to discover some intresting flavors. The main dishes are nicely presented and I really liked my ox cheeks, they were almost as good as when I am cooking them myself ( ;-)). The wine card presents something for almost each preference ...", "To sum it up: a nice place in the middle of the City, where you can have a reasonably priced classy business lunch or dinner."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d1386832", "id_comment": "g186338-d1386832-r118701657", "resto": "Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d1386832-Reviews-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "Missing Something", "diner_date": null, "rating_date": "28 September 2011", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Ron S", "reviewer_origin": ["London"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "242"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "124"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Atmosphere", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["30", "20", "20", "30"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d1386832-r118701657-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "content": ["It's was not the worse restaurant but certainly nowhere near the best.", "Unfortunately the meal lacked flavour and was on the bland side.", "The waiter was polite even though his customer care was a bit staged.", "Decent portions of food just not that inspiring."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d1386832", "id_comment": "g186338-d1386832-r101191565", "resto": "Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d1386832-Reviews-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "rating": "2", "title": "Downright bad, 3/10", "diner_date": " March 2011", "rating_date": "22 March 2011", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "lava_tory", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "48"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "63"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Atmosphere", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["20", "20", "10", "20"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d1386832-r101191565-Cinnamon_Restaurant_and_Bar-London_England.html", "content": ["Work. Sleep three hours. Get up with aching arms and legs and fly. Travel all the way across London and arrive at hotel. ", "Well, of course we fell straight asleep, and by the time we managed to wake up it was getting a bit late to go anywhere else than here. Never again, even if I have to stay awake 24 hours plus.", "So, where to start? The service, I guess. Unfortunately our waiter didn't have much understanding of English and had to be helped out constantly by his colleague, who was only marginally better. They gave the impression of pretty serious incompetence, even in a completely empty restaurant. Of course, there was no atmosphere as a result of this - the sterile decor didn't help.", "On to the food - my bream dish had three elements on the plate, and these tasted spicy, spicy and, er, spicy. The fish, coated with a layer of courgette slices, was actually cooked for the correct length of time, but was spiced into oblivion and didn't seem too fresh. The crab, leek and pea ragu underneath it was absolutely vile, again spiced into oblivion but I could still manage to taste that the crab seemed tinned. The third element was harissa, which was decent enough but I'd had enough spice by now. In case you're wondering, I do actually like spicy food - even extremely hot food when called for - but not when the spices obscure all the other flavours on the plate. Another thing I would have liked here was a bit of crunch, there was nothing in this dish with any real bite resistance.", "My companion had lamb knuckle. This was marginally better but rather boring, particularly the limp-tasting sauce. Too much gristle remained in the lamb, and a piece of string had somehow made its way onto the plate. ", "We shared a chocolate & chilli fondant for dessert, this was better than either of the main courses but again uninspiring, the chilli taste was too subtle (must have all been used up in the bream) and was just dry heat without a trace of the fruitiness I was hoping for. ", "None of this was particularly cheap - I believe our mains were in the \u00a318 price range, which is quite excessive when the quality is sub-Cafe Rouge. I have guesstimated a price of \u00a335-40 for 3 courses exc drinks and service. This makes it a place to avoid with extreme prejudice."]}
